name: unifi-native
description: A Pulumi package for creating and managing Unifi OS resources.

allowInsecure.description: Implicitly trust the Unifi API server's TLS certificate. This is useful for testing, but should not be used in production.

apiHost.description: The URL Host name or IP Address for the Unifi API, e.g. 10.1.1.1

apiKey.description: The API key for an admin user, generated from the Unifi admin console

siteId.description: The Human readable Stack identifier (e.g. 'notDefault') for the Unifi site to manage. Defaults to 'default'

forWlanconf.description: Mark AP Group as dedicated for a single WLAN Conf (Devices view). It will be hidden from list results by default for backward compatibility, but possible to enable optionally

repeatOnDays.description: Repeat on on days. Applicable to: EVERY_WEEK, CUSTOM

timeAllDay.description: Rule will be running for all day. Time range start/end are ignored. Applicable to: EVERY_WEEK, CUSTOM

timeRangeEnd.description: End time in 24 hours format. It accepts 24:00 as end of the day. Applicable to: EVERY_DAY, EVERY_WEEK, ONE_TIME_ONLY, CUSTOM

timeRangeStart.description: Start time in 24 hours format. Applicable to: EVERY_DAY, EVERY_WEEK, ONE_TIME_ONLY, CUSTOM
